  "texts": [
    "Let i (f i, π i) be a regular formal Lipschitz sum with s( i (f i, π i)) ≤ S. Let h be given by the formula from Lemma 5.9 and recall that then h is finitely L-biLipschitz.",
    "Therefore, by Corollary 5.16, there exists an admissible rectangle R ∈ R k for some k ≤ k 0 such that h has ε-property 1 on R. By definition, this means that there is some n ∈ {0,..., K -2} an admissible cubeQ = Q(R, n) of order k, such that ∥h(x + τ) -h(x) - 1 N M (h(r(R)) -h(l(R)))∥ 2 ≤ ε N M (N M) k 2.",
    "By the definition of h, in particular∞ i=1 d j=1 L d-2 i [π j i (x + τ) -π j i (x) - 1 N M (π j i (r(R)) -π j i (l(R)))] 2 ≤ ε N M (N M) k 2, (5.20) for every x ∈ Q.",
    "We let W i = 1 N M (π i (r(R)) -π i (l(R))).",
    "Note that now the left hand side of (5.20) reads as∞ i=1 d j=1 L d-2 i [π j i (x + τ) -π j i (x) -W j i] 2 = ∞ i=1 L d-2 i ∥π i (x + τ) -π i (x) -W i ∥ 2 = i L d-2 i ∥π i (x) -πi (x)∥ 2,where the Pythagoras's theorem was used in the first equality."
